x4freetext: The stacks of zirconium foils (12.9 mg/cm**2).
These stacks were interlaid by copper foils during
the irradiation.
A check of half-life and gamma-ray energies
was carried out.
Uncertainties in the cross section values were
estimated by propagating in quadrature the
contributions from:
* both decay curve and peak analyses (the latter
including counting statistics),
* absolute detector efficiencies,
* disintegration schemes,
* target thicknesses
* alpha particle flux.
Uncertainty in the energy straggling losses
